Tungsten is a framework for building compilers. It is currently under
active development by Jay Conrod.

Build dependencies:
Scala 2.8.0
Buildr 1.4.1
JUnit 4.6

Run dependencies:
Scala 2.8.0
LLVM 2.7 (for LLVM bridge)


To build tungsten and the LLVM bridge and run unit tests:
buildr

To assemble a Tungsten source file:
scala tungsten.Assembler foo.w

To disassemble a Tungsten module:
scala tungsten.Disassembler foo.wo

To link a Tungsten module into a program:
scala tungsten.Linker -t program foo.wo -o foo.wp

To link a Tungsten module into a library:
scala tungsten.Linker -t library -n foo -v 1.0 foo.wo -o foo.wl

To convert a Tungsten module to LLVM source:
scala tungsten.llvm.TungstenToLlvm foo.wo
